{"title":"Synthesis Projects","markdown":{"yaml":{"page-layout":"full","title":"Synthesis Projects"},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n\nIn 2021, UKRI [funded](https://www.ukri.org/opportunity/synthesising-evidence-in-economics-of-biodiversity/) nine short projects to synthesise current knowledge and evidence in the economics of biodiversity. \n\nThe following documents present the outcomes of these projects:\n\n<br />\n\n::: {.grid}\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-AssigningEconomicValueBiodiversityPromisePerilsBiodiversityCredits.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Assigning economic value to biodiversity: the promise and perils of biodiversity credits</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Richard Field, University of Nottingham</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-BiodiversityWaterCycleRewildingMitigateImpactsHydrologicalExtremes.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Biodiversity and the water cycle: can rewilding mitigate the impacts of hydrological extremes?</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Dr Gemma Harvey, Queen Mary University of London</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-BiodiversityMetricsPublicPreferencesCostBasedApproach-FullReport.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Biodiversity metrics and biodiversity values for the public appraisal of biodiversity: synthesising and extending the evidence</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Ben Groom, University of Exeter</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-ReviewEcosystemModellingFrameworksSupportDevelopmentIntegratedModelsEcosystemManagement.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Core principles for integrated models for ecosystem management</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Dr Daniel Bearup, University of Kent</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-EconomicBenefitsPollinationGlobalFoodSystems-FullReport.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Economic benefits of pollination to global food systems - evidence and knowledge gaps</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Simon Potts, University of Reading</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-RewardingLandownersLandManagersConservingBiodiversity.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Rewarding landowners and land managers for conserving biodiversity</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Nick Hanley, University of Glasgow</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-SynthesisCriticalAssessmentManagementToolsMainstreamBiodiversityDecisionMakingPrivateSector.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Synthesis and critical assessment of management tools to mainstream biodiversity in decision-making in the private sector</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Dr Pamela Katic, University of Greenwich</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-SynthesisingEvidenceEconomicsFarmEnvironmentalBiodiversity-FullReport.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Synthesizing evidence in the economics of farm environmental biodiversity</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Riccardo Scarpa, University of Durham</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-UnderstandingEconomicRecoveryPotentialInvestingBiodiversityGlobalSouth-FullReport.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Understanding the economic recovery potential of investing in biodiversity in the Global South</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Nathalie Seddon, University of Oxford</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n:::","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n\nIn 2021, UKRI [funded](https://www.ukri.org/opportunity/synthesising-evidence-in-economics-of-biodiversity/) nine short projects to synthesise current knowledge and evidence in the economics of biodiversity. \n\nThe following documents present the outcomes of these projects:\n\n<br />\n\n::: {.grid}\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-AssigningEconomicValueBiodiversityPromisePerilsBiodiversityCredits.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Assigning economic value to biodiversity: the promise and perils of biodiversity credits</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Richard Field, University of Nottingham</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-BiodiversityWaterCycleRewildingMitigateImpactsHydrologicalExtremes.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Biodiversity and the water cycle: can rewilding mitigate the impacts of hydrological extremes?</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Dr Gemma Harvey, Queen Mary University of London</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-BiodiversityMetricsPublicPreferencesCostBasedApproach-FullReport.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Biodiversity metrics and biodiversity values for the public appraisal of biodiversity: synthesising and extending the evidence</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Ben Groom, University of Exeter</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-ReviewEcosystemModellingFrameworksSupportDevelopmentIntegratedModelsEcosystemManagement.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Core principles for integrated models for ecosystem management</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Dr Daniel Bearup, University of Kent</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-EconomicBenefitsPollinationGlobalFoodSystems-FullReport.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Economic benefits of pollination to global food systems - evidence and knowledge gaps</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Simon Potts, University of Reading</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-RewardingLandownersLandManagersConservingBiodiversity.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Rewarding landowners and land managers for conserving biodiversity</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Nick Hanley, University of Glasgow</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-SynthesisCriticalAssessmentManagementToolsMainstreamBiodiversityDecisionMakingPrivateSector.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Synthesis and critical assessment of management tools to mainstream biodiversity in decision-making in the private sector</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Dr Pamela Katic, University of Greenwich</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-SynthesisingEvidenceEconomicsFarmEnvironmentalBiodiversity-FullReport.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Synthesizing evidence in the economics of farm environmental biodiversity</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Riccardo Scarpa, University of Durham</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.g-col-12}\n\n<div class=\"card card-synthesis\">\n<div class=\"card-body\">\n<a href=\"https://www.ukri.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/NERC-281022-UnderstandingEconomicRecoveryPotentialInvestingBiodiversityGlobalSouth-FullReport.pdf\" class=\"stretched-link\"></a>\n<h5 class=\"card-title\">Understanding the economic recovery potential of investing in biodiversity in the Global South</h5>\n<p class=\"card-subtitle\">Principal Investigator: Professor Nathalie Seddon, University of Oxford</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n:::"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"H